<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="535" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1786,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis box="[199,380,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer caudo-ventrally rounded with tooth-like short process. Subgenital plate with emargination on lateral margin near apex. Style with prominent subapical lobe, apophysis slender, strongly laterally curved. Aedeagal shaft elongate, membranous except for a narrow dorsal sclerotized rod; preatrial processes bladelike, with ventral margin expanded subapically and strongly serrated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1786,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis box="[199,369,1967,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 4.0 mm long and 
<quantity box="[635,721,1967,1991]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 
<quantity box="[1017,1103,1967,1991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
long and 1.0 mm wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
